newCmd('','13.3.6','','','starts capturing to the designated GIF file.  Whether the animation loops or not depends upon the value of {#.animation~animation mode}: PALINDROME or LOOP results in a looping GIF (no distinction, as there is no PALINDROME option in GIF animation) or ONCE (no looping). Frame rate is determined by {#.animation~animation fps}, which has a maximum of 50 frames per second.','*2','&quot;filename.gif&quot;','')
