newCmd('.navigate','11.1.1','','*v+11.2 -- new;nav','The <b>navigate</b> command allows exploring of the model from the perspective of an airplane capable of flying through the model. In each case, an optional time in seconds determines the  time to reach the objective. If no time is given, the change occurs over two seconds. (In the case of PATH, this is the time to each point along the path, not the total path.) Subcommands can be grouped in the same command by separating them with "/", for example: <b>navigate 2 DEPTH 30 / 5 ROTATE 180 / DEPTH 20 / TRANSLATE X 10</b>.','0|1','','')
