newCmd('','11.1.5','','*v+11.2;','Sets the slab/depth plane based on a plane using the general syntax for {#.plane expressions~}. For example: <b>slab PLANE {{atomno=3}} {{atomno=2}} {{atomno=1}}; slab on</b>. Note that the order of points defines the direction from the plane of atoms to be removed. If using your right hand to define the path from first point to second to third, your right thumb points to the atoms removed by slabbing. (Opposite this for <b>depth</b>.)','*41','PLANE','plane_expression or NONE')
