newCmd('.try','','','*v+12.0 - new;flow','Surrounding a set of Jmol script with try{{...}} and following it by catch(e){{...}} allows the catching of errors within larger blocks of script. The action is the same as in JavaScript. For example, in the following, the first model is never lost, and no error message is printed in the applet window.  Any variables created with the VAR keyword are local to the try or catch block.<br /><br />load quartz.cif<br />refresh<br />while(true) {{ <br />&nbsp;&nbsp; try {{<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  load files "caffeine.xyz" "1d.pdb"<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; }} catch(e) {{<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  prompt @{{"oops -- " + e}}<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; break;<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;}}<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; prompt "File loaded successfully"<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; break;<br />}}','1|2','','')
